  40,2,"The revelation of this Book is from God‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Knowing"
  40,3,"the Forgiver of sin and Accepter of repentance, the Severe in punishment, and Infinite in bounty. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. To Him ňĻaloneňļ is the final return"
  40,4,"None disputes the signs of God except the disbelievers, so do not be deceived by their prosperity throughout the land"
  40,5,"Before them, the people of Noah denied ňĻthe truthňļ, as did ňĻotherňļ enemy forces afterwards. Every community plotted against its prophet to seize him, and argued in falsehood, ňĻhopingňļ to discredit the truth with it. So I seized them. And how ňĻhorribleňļ was My punishment"
  40,6,And so your Lord‚Äôs decree has been proven true against the disbelievers‚ÄĒthat they will be the inmates of the Fire
  40,7,"Those ňĻangelsňļ who carry the Throne and those around it glorify the praises of their Lord, have faith in Him, and seek forgiveness for the believers, ňĻpraying:ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! You encompass everything in ňĻYourňļ mercy and knowledge. So forgive those who repent and follow Your Way, and protect them from the torment of the Hellfire"
  40,8,"Our Lord! Admit them into the Gardens of Eternity which You have promised them, along with the righteous among their parents, spouses, and descendants. You ňĻaloneňļ are truly the Almighty, All-Wise"
  40,9,And protect them from ňĻthe consequences of theirňļ evil deeds. For whoever You protect from the evil of their deeds on that Day will have been shown Your mercy. That is ňĻtrulyňļ the ultimate triumph.‚ÄĚ
  40,10,"Indeed, it will be announced to the disbelievers, ‚ÄúGod‚Äôs contempt for you‚ÄĒas you disbelieved when invited to belief‚ÄĒwas far worse than your contempt for one another ňĻTodayňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  40,11,"They will plead, ‚ÄúOur Lord! You made us lifeless twice, and gave us life twice.¬†Now we confess our sins. So is there any way out?‚ÄĚ"
  40,12,"ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúňĻNo!ňļ This is because when God alone was invoked, you ňĻstaunchlyňļ disbelieved. But when others were associated with Him ňĻin worshipňļ, you ňĻreadilyňļ believed. So ňĻTodayňļ judgment belongs to God ňĻaloneňļ‚ÄĒthe Most High, All-Great.‚ÄĚ"
  40,13,He is the One Who shows you His signs and sends down ňĻrain asňļ a provision for you from the sky. ňĻButňļ none will be mindful except those who turn ňĻto Himňļ
  40,14,"So call upon God with sincere devotion, even to the dismay of the disbelievers"
  40,15,"ňĻHe isňļ Highly Exalted in rank, Lord of the Throne. He sends down the revelation by His command to whoever He wills of His servants to warn ňĻallňļ of the Day of Meeting‚ÄĒ"
  40,16,"the Day all will appear ňĻbefore Godňļ. Nothing about them will be hidden from Him. ňĻHe will ask,ňļ ‚ÄúWho does all authority belong to this Day? To God‚ÄĒthe One, the Supreme"
  40,17,Today every soul will be rewarded for what it has done. No injustice Today! Surely God is swift in reckoning.‚ÄĚ
  40,18,"Warn them ňĻO Prophetňļ of the approaching Day when the hearts will jump into the throats, suppressing distress. The wrongdoers will have neither a close friend nor intercessor to be heard"
